\section{Synthetic Data Generation}
%=============================================================================

\subsection{Overview}

Synthetic data generation addresses the scarcity of parking enforcement vehicle images by using generative AI to insert vehicles into empty frames.

\subsection{Method}

The synthesis pipeline used Google's Gemini API with the following configuration:

\begin{itemize}
	\item API: Google Gemini (gemini-3-pro-image-preview)
	\item Edit types: Vehicle insertion into empty frames
	\item Classes generated: enforcement\_vehicle, police\_old, police\_new
	\item Image resizing: Cover-resize + center-crop to (640, 610)
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Console Output}

The synthesis completed successfully after processing all candidates:

\begin{lstlisting}[language=bash, basicstyle=\ttfamily\scriptsize]
Synthesizing: 100%|======...======| 1471/1471 [1:11:33<00:00]
2026-03-03 03:48:11 - INFO - Created 2658 synthetic images
2026-03-03 03:48:11 - INFO - Manifest updated: manifests/images.csv
\end{lstlisting}

\subsection{Output}

The synthesis produced the following results:

\begin{table}[H]
	\centering
	\begin{tabular}{lr}
		\toprule
		\textbf{Metric}          & \textbf{Value}      \\
		\midrule
		Input empty frames       & 1,471               \\
		Synthetic images created & 2,658               \\
		Generation time          & 1 hour 11 minutes   \\
		Output location          & data/images\_synth/ \\
		\bottomrule
	\end{tabular}
	\caption{Synthetic data generation statistics}
\end{table}

\noindent\textbf{Cost Efficiency:} The entire synthesis operation cost only \$6.23 in Gemini API credits, demonstrating the cost-effectiveness of generative AI for dataset augmentation compared to traditional data collection methods.

\subsection{Iteration Speed from Synthetic Gating and Gemini Generation}

An important practical advantage of this pipeline is iteration speed. Before synthesis, candidate frames are filtered through synthetic gating so only valid street/road scenes are promoted, while non-road and non-street images are routed out of the generation path. In our runs, this reduced the estimated human review effort from approximately 5--6 hours to about 1.5 hours by reducing wasted synthesis calls and manual cleanup time.

Gemini-based generation then produces class-targeted variants directly from approved empty frames, which allows the team to rebalance scarce classes (especially enforcement vehicles) in a single run instead of waiting for additional real-world data collection. Together, gating and controlled synthetic generation create a tighter feedback loop: update prompts or thresholds, regenerate focused samples, retrain, and evaluate quickly.


\subsection{Next Steps}

Following synthesis, the dataset requires manual review:

\begin{enumerate}
	\item Review synthetic images for quality and realism
	\item Delete nonsensical or failed generations
	\item Verify bounding box labels match inserted vehicles
\end{enumerate}


